{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyMOniuk0ldD1XU1hW92QpKA"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Modelo AR(P):\n","\n","Este se calcula con la ecuacion\n","\n","$$ X_t = c + \\sum_{i=1}^{\\text{p}} \\phi_i X_{t-i} + Z_t .$$\n","\n","Como queremos usar la teoria de ecuacines en diferencias, convertimos esta ecuacion a un polinomio caraceristico de orden $n$ mediante el uso del backshift operator.\n","\n","Pasando todo lo que tenga $X$ a la izquierda\n","\n","Esta es una ecuacion en diferencias de orden $n$.\n","\n","Usando, exactamente, los metodos para ordenes 1 y 2:\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","(1 - \\phi_1 B - \\phi_2 B^2 - \\cdots - \\phi_{\\text{p}} B^p) X_t = c + Z_t\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","donde\n","\n","$$p(B)= 1 - \\phi_1 B - \\phi_2 B^2 - \\cdots - \\phi_{\\text{p}} B^{\\text{p}} $$\n","es el polinomio caracteristico del sistema.\n","\n","La solucion analitica se encuentra en tres pasos\n","1. Solucion particular\n","2. Solucion homogenea (=0)\n","3. Combinacion de las dos anteriores para producir la solucion.\n","\n","\n","## Solucion particular\n","\n","El proceso es el mismo donde\n","\n","$$p(B) X_t = c + Z_t$$,\n","y algebraicamente la soucion particular de este sistema es\n","\n","$$X_t = \\frac{c + Z_t}{p(B)} $$\n","\n","Lo que pasa es que quien es?  $1/p(B)$. Realmente $p(B)$ es un operador\n","y toca resolverlo con fracciones parciales. \n","\n","Lo tendriamos que factorizar.\n","\n","$$p(B) = (1 - \\varphi_1 B)^{m_1}(1 - \\varphi_2 B)^{m_2} \\cdots (1 - \\varphi_k B^k)^{m_k} $$"],"metadata":{"id":"PFyNZXoOiy_1"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["En esta factorizacion hay un total de $k$ raices con repeticiones.\n","Es decir $m_1 + m_2 + \\cdots + m_k=p$. Yo podria factoriazar \"afuera\" cada $\\varphi_i$ y escribir en vez\n","\n","\n","$$ p(B) = \\varphi_1^{m_1} \\varphi_2^{m_2} \\cdots \\varphi_k^{m_k} \\left ( \\frac{1}{\\varphi_1} - B  \\right )^{m_1} \\left (\\frac{1}{\\varphi_2} - B \\right )^{m_2} \\cdots \\left (\\frac{1}{\\varphi_k} - B \\right )^{m_k} $$ \n","\n","De forma que (recuerde que $r_i=1/\\varphi_i$), y usando fracciones parciales.\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\frac{1}{p(B)} &=& \\frac{1}{ \\varphi_1^{m_1} \\varphi_2^{m_2} \\cdots \\varphi_k^{m_k} \\left ( \\frac{1}{\\varphi_1} - B  \\right )^{m_1} \\left (\\frac{1}{\\varphi_2} - B \\right )^{m_2} \\cdots \\left (\\frac{1}{\\varphi_k} - B \\right )^{m_k}} \\\\\n","&=& \\frac{1}{r_1^{m_1} r_2^{m_2} \\cdots r_k^{m_k}  \\left ( r_1 - B  \\right )^{m_1} \\left (r_2 - B \\right )^{m_2} \\cdots \\left (r_k  - B \\right )^{m_k}} \\\\\n","&=& r_1^{m_1} r_2^{m_2} \\cdots r_k^{m_k}  \\left ( \n","    \\sum_{i=1}^{m_1} \\frac{A_{i1}}{(r_1 - B)^i} + \\sum_{i=1}^{m_2} \\frac{A_{i2}}{(r_2 - B)^i} + \\cdots + \\sum_{i=1}^{m_k} \\frac{A_{ik}}{(r_k - B)^i}\n","    \\right )\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","\n","Cada una de esas fracciones toca extenderla a una serie geometrica. Por ejemplo, tomemos un $j$ en la secuencia $j=1,2, \\cdots, m_i$ y un $i$, $i=1,2, \\cdots , k$.\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\frac{A_{ij}}{(r_j - B)^i} = \\frac{A_{ij}}{r_j^{i}\\left (1 - \\frac{B}{r_j}  \\right )} = \\frac{A_{ij}}{r_j^i} \\left ( 1 + \\frac{B}{r_j} +  \\left (  \\frac{B}{r_j} \\right )^2 + \\cdots + \\left ( \\frac{B}{r_j} \\right )^l + \\cdots  \\right )\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","Esta es apenas una de las fracciones parciales. Como se aplica esta fraccion a la serie $X_t$, para $m_k=1$ \n","\n","$$ \\frac{A_{1j}}{r_j -B} X_t = \\frac{A_{ij}}{r_j^{i}\\left (X_t - \\frac{1}{r_j}  \\right )} = \\frac{A_{ij}}{r_j^i} \\left ( X_t + \\frac{1}{r_j} X_{t-1} +  \\left (  \\frac{1}{r_j}  \\right )^2 X_{t-2}  + \\cdots + \\left ( \\frac{1}{r_j} \\right )^l  X_{t-l} + \\cdots  \\right )$$\n","\n","Pero profe, esto esta a una potencia.\n","\n","$$ \\left ( \\frac{A_{1j}}{r_j -B} \\right )^{m_i} X_t$$.\n","Lo que se hace es que aplica $m_i$ veces el operator de arriba.\n","\n","## La homogenea. (=0)\n","En forma polinomial esta se escribe como\n","\n","$$(1 - \\phi_1 B - \\phi_2 B^2 - \\cdots \\phi_i B^i) X_t = 0  $$\n","Como se resuelve?\n","\n","Primero factorizamos el polinomio caracteristico\n","\n","$$ p(B) = (1 - \\varphi_1 B)^{m_1} (1 - \\varphi_2 B)^{m_2} \\cdots (1 - \\varphi_k)^{m_k} $$\n","\n","El problema que tenemos que resolver es \n","\n","$$ p(B) X_t = 0 $$\n","y encontrar la solucion $X_t$ (esto se llama **modelamiento**, en contraste con **inversion** que es cuando de los datos $X_t$ obtenemos $\\phi_i$. )\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","Cada uno de los factores producen una ecuacion. Por ejemplo si \n","$ab=0$, entonces $a=0$ o $b=0$. \n","\n","Una de estas es\n","\n","$$ (1 - \\varphi B)^{m} X_t = 0  \\quad (1)  $$.\n","Cada $m$ en esta ultima ecuacion puede ser $m_1, m_2, \\cdots , m_k$ tiene\n","$m$ raices repetidas. El problema ya lo resolvimos para $m=2$ (AR(2)).\n","Este lo vamos a resolver de forma similar.\n","\n","Los pasos son:\n","\n","* Resolver $(1 - B)^m x_t = 0$ (ya lo hicimos para $m=2$). Note que este es es un caso particular de la ecuacion (1) con $\\varphi=1$). De la misma forma que hicimos para $m=2$, aseguramos que la solucion es de la forma\n","$X_t = C_j t^j$, $j=0,1, \\cdots, m-1$, donde $C_j$ son coeficientes que se pueden encontrar con las condiciones iniciales. Esto toca verificarlo y lo vamos a hacer por induccion matematica:\n","\n","Si $m=1$, ya lo hicimos, pero repitamoslo, para $m=1$ la solucion\n","es $X_0= C_0 t^0 = C_0=C$\n","\n","$$ (1 - B)X_j = (1-B) X_0 = (1-B) C = C - BC = C- C = 0 $$.\n","\n","Asumamos que para cualquier exponente  menor que $m$ es valido (induccion) y lo\n","aplicamos para $m$. la solucion es de la forma $C t^j$, donde $C$ es\n","alguna constante. $j=0,1,2, \\cdots, m-1$. \n","\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","(1 - B)^m X_t &=& (1 - B)^{m-1} (1-B) C t^j  \\\\\n","&=& (1 - B)^{m-1} C (t^j - (t-1)^j) \\\\\n","&=& (1 - B)^{m-1} C \\left ( t^j - \\sum_{i=0}^j \\binom{i}{j} t^j (-1)^{j-i} \\right ) \\\\\n","&=& (1 - B)^{m-1} C \\left ( t^j - t^j - \\sum_{i=0}^{j-1} \\binom{i}{j} t^j (-1)^{j-i} \\right ) \\\\\n","&=& (1 - B)^{m-1} C \\left ( - \\sum_{i=0}^{j-1} \\binom{i}{j} t^j (-1)^{j-i} \\right ) \\\\\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","Aplicamos la hipotesis de induccion. Cada termino de la suma de la derecha tiene como potencia $t^l$, donde $l \\le m-2$. Todos esos terminos\n","se hacen 0. De forma que\n","\n","$$(1 - B)^{m} X_t = 0 $$\n","donde $X_t = C t^j$, $j=0,1, \\cdots, m-1$. \n","\n","El problema que nos corresponde es $(1- \\varphi B)^m X_t=0$ (ecuacion (1)).\n","\n","Aseguramos que la solucion (como se hizo para el caso AR(2))\n","$X_t = C_j t^j \\varphi^t$, conde $C_j$ son constantes y $j=0,1, \\cdots, m-1$. La solucion general homogenea es una combinacion lineal de estas.\n","\n","Veamos que en verdad esa es la solucion, en el termino lineal y luego\n","el termino a la $m$. \n","\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","(1 - \\varphi B) X_t &=& (1 - \\varphi B)( C_j t^j \\varphi^t) \\\\\n","&=& C_j t^j \\varphi^t - C_j \\varphi (t-1)^j \\varphi^{t-1} \\\\\n","&=& C_j ( t^j \\varphi^t - \\varphi(t-1) \\varphi^{t-1}) \\\\\n","&=& C_j \\varphi^t (t^j - (t-1)^j) \\\\\n","&=& C_j \\varphi^t (1 - B) t^j \\\\\n","&=& 0\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","por la derivacion anterior con $\\varphi=1$. \n","\n","## La solucion homogenea es la combinacion lineal de todas las soluciones homogeneas. Es decir.\n","\n","$$X_{th} = \\sum_{i=1}^k \\sum_{j=0}^{m_k-1} C_{ij} t^j \\varphi_i^t $$\n","\n","Finalmente la solucion es \n","\n","$$X_t = X_{tp} + X_{th} $$\n","\n","y toca hallar todos los coeficientes $C_{ij}$ con las p condiciones iniciales. \n","\n","Como en general es complicado, nosotros desde el punto de vista numerico\n","aplicamos la solucion iterada\n","\n","\n","$$ X_t = c + \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i X_{t-i} + Z_t $$\n","comenzando con las condiciones iniciales dadas $X_0, X_1, \\cdots , X_{\\mathrm{p}-1}$\n","\n","Con esto queda planteado el problema general. No existe solucion cerrada. Solo existe el algoritmos que aca planteo. Para $m=3,4$ existen soluciones cerradas. \n","\n","\n","# Propiedades estadisticas (parametros) se las series de tiempo AR(p).\n","\n","Se asume que las series son estacionarias.\n","\n","## Media (Esperanza):\n","\n","$$\\mu = \\mathbb{E}[X_t] = \\mathrm{E}[c] + \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\mathbb{E}[ \\phi_i X_{t-i}] + \\mathbb{Z_t} = c + \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\mu + 0 . $$\n","\n","Despejamos $\\mu$.\n","\n","$$\\mu \\left ( 1 - \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\right ) = c $$\n","\n","y\n","\n","$$\\mu = \\frac{c}{1 - \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i} $$\n","Esta es la **media** de un modelo AR(p). Si $c=0$ la media es $0$. \n","\n","## Varianza.\n","\n","$$ X_t = c + \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i X_{t-i} + Z_t $$\n","De aca:  $c=0$\n","\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\gamma_k &=& \\mathbb{E}[ X_t X_{t-k}] =\\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\mathbb{E}[X_{t-i} X_{t-k}] + \\mathbb{E}[Z_t X_{t-k}] = \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\gamma_{k-i} + \\mathbb{E}[Z_t X_{t-k}]\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","Pero\n","\n","\n","\n","  \\begin{eqnarray*}\n","      \\mathbb{E}[Z_t X_{t-k} ] = \\left \\{   %}\n","      \\begin{array}{cc}\n","        \\sigma_Z^2 & \\text{if  } k = 0 \\\\\n","        0 &  \\text{      if        } k=1,2, \\cdots \n","      \\end{array}\n","      \\right  .\n","    \\end{eqnarray*}\n","\n","\n","Encontramos las siguientes ecuaciones:\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\sigma^2 &=& \\gamma_0 = \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\gamma_{-i} + \\sigma_Z^2 \\quad, \\quad k=0 \\\\\n","\\gamma_k &=& \\sum_{i=1}^p \\phi_i \\gamma_{k-i} \\quad , \\quad k=1,2, \\cdots\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","Estamos tentados a hallar la varianza de aca, es decir\n","\n","$$\\sigma^2 = \\gamma_0 = \\phi_1 \\gamma_1 + \\phi_2 \\gamma_2 + \\cdots + \\phi_{\\mathrm{p}} \\gamma_{\\mathrm{p}} + \\sigma_Z^2  $$\n","Aclaramos es que por la simetria de la autocorrelacion $\\gamma_{-i}=\\gamma_i$.\n","\n","Un problema es que no conocemos los $\\gamma_i$, $i=1,2, \\cdots , \n","\\mathrm{p}$.\n","\n","Podriamos usar que\n","\n","$$ \\rho_i = \\frac{\\gamma_i}{\\gamma_0} = \\frac{\\gamma_i}{\\sigma^2} $$\n","de donde $\\gamma_i = \\rho_i \\sigma^2$ y escribir:\n","\n","$$\\sigma^2 = \\gamma_0 = \\phi_1 \\rho_1 \\gamma_0  + \\phi_2 \\rho_2 \\gamma_0  + \\cdots + \\phi_{\\mathrm{p}} \\rho_{\\mathrm{p}} \\gamma_{0} + \\sigma_Z^2  $$\n","\n","factorizar y despejar $\\gamma_0 = \\sigma^2$ (que es la varianza. Lo que buscamos)\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"yOsl3dMRgllw"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["$$\\sigma^2 = \\gamma_0 = \\frac{\\sigma_Z^2}{1 - \\phi_1 \\rho_1 - \\phi_2 \\rho_2 - \\cdots -\\phi_{\\mathrm{p}} \\rho_{\\mathrm{p}}} $$\n","\n","El problema es que no conocemos los $\\rho_k$. En este caso\n","lo mejor que podemos hacer es usar los datos y hallar la varianza\n","de la formula de estimacion. No existe, en general, una formula analtica\n","de la varianza en funcion solo de los $\\phi_i$.\n","\n","## ACF. \n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\sigma^2 &=& \\gamma_0 = \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\gamma_{-i} + \\sigma_Z^2 \\quad, \\quad k=0 \\\\\n","\\gamma_k &=& \\sum_{i=1}^p \\phi_i \\gamma_{k-i} \\quad , \\quad k=1,2, \\cdots\n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","De estas dos ecuaciones de arriba, dividamoslas por $\\sigma^2= \\gamma_0$\n","y tenemos\n","\n","\\begin{eqnarray}\n","\\rho_0 &=& 1 \\\\\n","\\rho_k &=& \\sum_{i=1}^{\\mathrm{p}} \\phi_i \\rho_{k-i} \\quad , \\quad i=1,2, \\cdots \n","\\end{eqnarray}\n","\n","De nuevo (el problema del huevo y la gallina), por ejemplo\n","\n","$$\\rho_1 = \\phi_1 \\rho_0 + \\phi_2 \\rho_1 + \\phi_3 \\rho_2 + \\cdots \\phi_{\\mathrm{p}} \\rho_{\\mathrm{p}-1} $$\n","\n","Volemos a estar en problemas y necesitamos los otros $\\rho$s para hallar $\\rho_1$, \n","\n","la ACF se debe calcular a partir de los datos. \n","\n","Y con estos datos podemos calcular los $\\phi_i$ mediante el metodo\n","de Yule-Walker (va para proxima clase).\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"_3OE4Oor13Bx"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n"],"metadata":{"id":"dBqcjG0ppE9E"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}